snippet: North Dakota State’s 35-7 victory capped a 15-0 season and marked Coach Craig Bohl’s final game with the team.
abstract: College Football Roundup; North Dakota State gets their perfect ending, capping a 15-0 season with a 35-7 victory over Towson in Frisco, Tex, to claim their third straight Football Championship Subdivision title; other news noted.
lead_paragraph: North Dakota State’s 35-7 victory capped a 15-0 season and marked Coach Craig Bohl’s final game with the team.

headline.main: North Dakota State Claims Its Third F.C.S. Title in a Row by Rolling Past Towson
headline.print_headline: North Dakota State Claims Its Third F.C.S. Title in a Row by Rolling Past Towson
